
//Video filename is  singleball.avi
//Colour of object to be tracked is green
//Delay is set as video is just two second, so we want to make sure we can see the object tracking properly by adding delay
//Drawpath is also set which will draw the path of the tracked object using red crosses

//Now testing what output is given when a name value pair argument is mispelled, in this case it is the colour green
KalmanFilter("FileName","singleball.avi","colour","gren","delay","true","drawpath","true");
          
//                                                                                 !--error 999 
//output->The colour entered was mispelled or it is not there in the options of colour to track
 
//Now testing what output is given when a name value pair argument is mispelled, in this case it is the colour green
KalmanFilter("FileName","juggling.mp4","colour","gren","delay","true","drawpath","true");
          
//                                                                                 !--error 999 
//output->The colour entered was mispelled or it is not there in the options of colour to track
 
//Now testing what output is given when a name value pair argument is mispelled, in this case it is the colour green
KalmanFilter("FileName","ped.avi","colour","gren","delay","true","drawpath","true");
          
//                                                                                 !--error 999 
//output->The colour entered was mispelled or it is not there in the options of colour to track
 

